article.headline: Duquesne 24, Sacred Heart 21
article.story: PITTSBURGH, Pa. (AP) -- Scott Knapp threw three touchdown passes to lead Duquesne to a 24-21 come-from-behind victory over Sacred Heart on Saturday. Knapp, who completed 21 of 29 passes for 259 yards, connected with Bruce Hocker on a pair of touchdown passes in the second quarter to rally the Dukes from a 14-0 deficit. The first covered 32 yards and capped a four-play, 57-yard drive. The second was for 33 yards and came on a six-play, 68-yard drive. Knapp also provided the deciding points for Duquesne (3-1) on a 22-yard touchdown pass to Conrad Carter with 5:41 left in the third quarter. The two-play, 27-yard drive was set up by Kyle Postell's interception of a pass by Sacred Heart's Tyler Arciaga. Sacred Heart (1-3) scored on its first two possessions on a 56-yard touchdown run by Jason Payne, and a 19-yard scoring pass from Arciaga to Alvin Franklin. Arciaga completed 16 of 28 passes for 203 yards and two touchdowns, but was intercepted twice and sacked twice. Arciaga gave Sacred Heart a 21-14 lead with a 44-yard touchdown pass to Corey Bundy with 2:09 left in the first half. Duquesne scored its only other points on the final play of the first half on a 37-yard field goal by Mark Troyan.
